	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real teenager — maybe you. The endless scroll that leaves you feeling behind. The grade that somehow became a verdict on your worth. The follower count you check more than you'd admit. The version of yourself you perform online while the real you feels unseen and lonely.</p><p>None of this means something is wrong with you. It means you're human, growing up in a world that ties your value to your performance and your popularity — and that's a weight no one was built to carry. There is a Father who sees the real you underneath all of it, and He has something to say about who you actually are.</p>`}
