	aFatherHeading={`A Father for teenagers`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you in the middle of being a teenager: the answer to the pressure isn't a higher GPA, a better following, or finally becoming the person you think you're supposed to be. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who already loves you, today, exactly as you are.</p><p>You were not made to earn your worth. You were made to receive it. And the One who made you doesn't grade you, rank you, or compare you to anyone. He calls you His beloved child — not the future you, not the impressive you, but <em>you</em>, right now, in this messy, in-between season.</p><p>So before you're a student, an athlete, an achiever, a name in a group chat — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady voice underneath all the noise, the one who says: I see you, I'm proud of you, and there is nothing you could do to make Me love you more — or less.</p>`}
