	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for teenagers?`, answer: `Psalm 139:14 (fearfully and wonderfully made), Jeremiah 29:11 (plans for a future and a hope), Philippians 4:6-7 (do not be anxious), Romans 8:38-39 (nothing can separate you from God's love), 1 Timothy 4:12 (don't let anyone look down on you for being young), Isaiah 43:1 (I have called you by name, you are Mine), and Zephaniah 3:17 (He rejoices over you) all speak straight to what teenagers carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about anxiety for teens?`, answer: `Scripture takes your anxiety seriously and offers a real place to put it. Philippians 4:6-7 says don't be anxious about anything, but bring your requests to God, and His peace will guard your heart and mind. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a Father you can actually hand the pressure to — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Does God love me even when my life feels like a mess?`, answer: `Yes — and that's the whole point. Your worth was never your grades or your performance. Romans 8:38-39 says nothing can separate you from God's love, and 1 Samuel 16:7 says He looks at your heart, not your surface. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet God as a Father who delights in you right now, not the fixed-up version you're trying to become. Read it free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
