		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for teens and youth?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — perfect for listening on the bus, before a test, or when anxiety hits late at night.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for teenagers?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of reading one more voice telling you to measure up, you meet the One who already delights in you. For a teen under constant pressure to perform, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a loved child first, not a project to be graded. Read it free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `How can I start reading the Bible as a teenager?`, answer: `Start small and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, pick a short book or a Psalm, and listen to the audio while you read. Try a verse a day — Psalm 139, Philippians 4, or Romans 8 are great places to begin. Our how-to-pray guide and verses-by-topic pages can help you find words for whatever you're facing right now.` },
